[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There are two kinds of AI tools. Those that make you adapt to AI, forcing you to learn the language, become an expert just to get basic work done and those that make AI adapt to you. For 2 years, we have been told the same thing, learn'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from engineering. An entire industry has sprung up teaching you how to speak AI. But why? Why should you change how you think to accommodate a tool? That\'s a reverse engineering. The tool should'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'understand you, not the other way around. So, we built something different. We build commands, over 100 commands that speak your language. Layout fixes to theme changes, image generation to content creation, code'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'refactoring to documentation. And this is just day one. We are building a command for every task you will ever need. This is pure precision without prompt engineering, speed without iteration. One of the builders shipped'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an entire SAS application in a single day. Changed the design theme thing, fixed the layout, integrated payment gateway, connected the database, rewrote every piece of copy to make it production ready, all with commands.'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is what AI should have been from day one. Not AI that makes you smaller. AI that makes you powerful. We call it precision mode and it\'s live today. Try commands to build production ready apps.'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Stop adapting, start commanding.'
